plot1 <- ggplot(a, aes(x = Region, y = TotalRevenue)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = "#2CB2F5") +
  geom_text(aes(label = scales::comma(TotalRevenue), y = TotalRevenue), vjust = -0.5, size = 3) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = unit_format(unit = "m", scale = 1e-6, sep = " ")) +
  labs(title = "Total Revenue by Region",
       x = "Regions",
       y = "Total Revenue (in millions)") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
        plot.background = element_rect(fill = "powderblue"),
        plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

plot2 <- ggplot(b, aes(x = Region, y = TotalProfit, group = 1)) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = unit_format(unit = "m", scale = 1e-6, sep = " ")) +
  geom_line(color = "#661EDA") +
  geom_point(color = "blue", size = 3) +
  labs(title = "Total Profit by Region",
       x = "Region",
       y = "Total Profit") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
        plot.background = element_rect(fill = "powderblue"),
        plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

plot3 <- ggplot(c_long, aes(x = ItemType, y = Value, fill = Metric)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge") +
  labs(title = "Unit Cost and Unit Price by ItemType",
       x = "ItemType",
       y = "Value") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("UnitCost" = "#2CB2F5", "UnitPrice" = "salmon")) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
        plot.background = element_rect(fill = "powderblue"))

plot4 <- ggplot(d, aes(x = ItemType, y = UnitsSold, group = SalesChannel, color = SalesChannel)) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(title = "Total Number of Items Sold by Sales Channel",
       x = "Item Type",
       y = "Units Sold")+
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
        plot.background = element_rect(fill = "powderblue"))

# Combine plots into a dashboard
dashboard <- plot_grid(plot1, plot2, plot3, plot4, nrow = 2)
